

## Version 6.2

- *TSPO PET imaging integration* ([Chapter 6, 1 new speculation environment; Chapter 7, 1 new limitation environment; Chapter 14k, 2 new hypothesis environments; Appendix H, 2 new annotated entries; references.bib, 8 new entries; hypothesis-registry.typ, 2 new entries]): Integration of 8-paper literature review on TSPO PET imaging in ME/CFS, highlighting critical methodological gaps and mechanistic insights. Single published ME/CFS TSPO PET study (Raijmakers 2021, n=9) found NO neuroinflammation using first-generation tracer; no whole-body TSPO PET studies exist in PubMed. Key finding: Barzon 2026 demonstrated peripheral inflammation reduces TSPO tracer brain influx (BBB transport confounding), potentially masking neuroinflammation. Added neuroinflammation measurement limitation environment to Chapter 7. Added TSPO dual-role speculation environment to Chapter 6 (mitochondrial dysfunction vs inflammation marker). Added two hypotheses to Chapter 14k: BBB transport confounding hypothesis (explains negative TSPO PET findings) and peripheral-inflation central-starvation hypothesis (resolves paradox of elevated peripheral TSPO with decreased brain signal). Updated hypothesis registry with 2 new entries. _Motivated by:_ @Raijmakers2021TSPOCFS — single ME/CFS TSPO PET study showing null neuroinflammation finding; @Barzon2026TSPOBBB — BB B transport confounding mechanism; @VanElzakker2019TSPOReview — comprehensive TSPO biology review. Michelle James Stanford conference data (unpublished) suggests whole-body TSPO imaging would reveal "peripheral-up, central-down" pattern, but study not yet in PubMed.
